        "a": "No. In the common case rep counting is a threshold state machine over one scalar signal — usually a joint angle — not a trained model. Google's own MediaPipe and ML Kit fitness samples count a rep when a signal crosses an enter threshold and then crosses back past an exit threshold, which is pure geometry plus a couple of thresholds."
