        "q": "What is the difference between the One-Euro filter and EMA for pose smoothing?",
        "a": "An EMA blends each new value with the running average at a fixed rate, which is cheap and good for scalar signals like a joint angle or a class probability. The One-Euro (1 euro) filter is an adaptive low-pass filter that uses position and velocity, lowering its cutoff when the body is still to kill jitter and raising it during fast motion to avoid lag. For raw landmark coordinates, One-Euro is preferred because it adapts to speed; it is MediaPipe Pose's built-in landmark smoother."
